WEBVTT

00:01.628 --> 00:02.642
Keep everyone back.

00:03.476 --> 00:05.082
You never were
much to look at.

00:05.638 --> 00:06.873
Oh, to us maybe.

00:06.907 --> 00:08.708
For all we know,
this one's a prime specimen,

00:08.742 --> 00:12.081
the Brad pitt
of Skitter world.

00:12.116 --> 00:14.518
Porter says we have to try
to communicate with this thing.

00:14.552 --> 00:16.755
Figure out how it thinks, we can
figure out how to beat it.

00:16.789 --> 00:19.858
You actually think you'll
figure a way to talk to it?

00:19.892 --> 00:21.929
I get it in a controlled
environment, give it a shot.

00:21.964 --> 00:25.433
A lot depends on what it's got
underneath the hood.

00:25.467 --> 00:27.838
I wouldn't
underestimate them.

00:27.872 --> 00:29.139
See the eyes?

00:29.173 --> 00:31.542
It's studying us as much
as we're studying them.

00:31.576 --> 00:33.643
I mean,
even if he wanted to chat,

00:33.677 --> 00:35.912
vocalizations could extend
above or below

00:35.946 --> 00:37.512
the range
of human hearing.

00:37.547 --> 00:38.813
I mean,
for all we know,

00:38.848 --> 00:40.982
he could be
cussing us out right now.

00:41.017 --> 00:42.950
I can almost
guarantee it.

00:44.552 --> 00:45.919
Get that damn thing
in the cage!

00:45.953 --> 00:48.788
All right, get that thing
in the cage! Get him in!

00:50.658 --> 00:52.026
Get him in there!

00:52.060 --> 00:56.199
Get him in there!

01:00.705 --> 01:02.006
Yeah.

01:03.810 --> 01:06.111
I remember you, too.

